      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The entity holding the money in escrow is typically a licensed real estate lawyer or a specialized trust company, rather than just a standard bank account. These professionals act as the impartial third party, which is vital because they are legally obligated to manage those funds according to the terms of the purchase agreement. They are the gatekeepers, ensuring that the seller gets paid *only* when the title transfers to you, and you get the house *only* when the funds are released. They are the professional guardians of the transaction's integrity.",
